%section.how-to#HowToInstall
  %h2 How To Install
  %h3 Installation - All Platforms
  %p Install the module with:
  :markdown
        :::bash
        npm install cylon-crazyflie

  %p
    You will also need to install the latest beta of firmware to the Crazyflie itself to use the 'hover' mode from
    =link_to "https://bitbucket.org/bitcraze/crazyflie-firmware/downloads/Crazyflie_2014.01.0.bin", "https://bitbucket.org/bitcraze/crazyflie-firmware/downloads/Crazyflie_2014.01.0.bin", target: :blank

  %h3 Ubuntu

  %p
    On Ubuntu, you will need to run:

  :markdown
        :::bash
        sudo apt-get install build-essential pkg-config libusb-1.0-0-dev

    before you will be able to run `npm install cylon-crazyflie`

  %h3 OSX
  :markdown
    On OSX, you will need to run:

        :::bash
        brew install libusb

    before you will be able to run `npm install cylon-crazyflie`



%section.how-to#HowToUse
  %h2 How To Use
  %p This small program causes the Crazyflie to takeoff for 10 seconds.
  :markdown
        :::javascript
        var Cylon = require('cylon');

        Cylon.robot({
          connection: { name: 'crazyflie', adaptor: 'crazyflie', port: 'radio://1/10/250KPS' },
          device: {name: 'drone', driver: 'crazyflie'},

          work: function(my) {
            my.drone.on('start', function() {
              my.drone.takeoff();
              after((10).seconds(), function() {
                my.drone.land();
              });
              after((15).seconds(), function() {
                my.drone.stop();
              });
            });
          }
        }).start();

  %h2 Hover Mode
  :markdown
        :::javascript
        my.drone.setParam('flightmode.althold', true);

  %h2 How to connect
  %p
    The Crazyflie uses a 2.4 GHz radio to communicate. There is a
    USB dongle called the Crazyradio that is required to control the Crazyflie quadcopter.
  %p
    If you are have a USB 3.0 port, you might run into this issue
    %br
    %a{ href: "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17204253/crazyflie-usb-3-0-incompability"} http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17204253/crazyflie-usb-3-0-incompability

  %h3 Ubuntu
  %p
    You need to install some udev-rules to be able to communicate with the crazyflie,
    it is a good thing that we have a
    %a{ href: "http://gort.io" } Gort
    command that does just that:

  :markdown
        :::bash
        $ gort crazyflie set-udev-rules

